  "prompt": "What happens to the photons when I switch off the light?",
  "response": "When you switch off the light, several things happen to the photons:\n\n1. No new photons are generated by the light source\n2. Existing photons continue traveling in their current direction\n3. These photons will:\n- Be absorbed by surfaces they encounter\n- Gradually dissipate their energy\n- Eventually stop or be transformed into other forms of energy (like heat)\n\nThe process is relatively quick, and the room becomes dark almost instantly as the light source stops emitting new photons.",
